# f-gemini-delete Privacy Policy

f-gemini-delete is a Chrome extension designed to help users batch select and delete Gemini web chat history on https://gemini.google.com/.

## Data We Collect

f-gemini-delete does not collect, sell, or share users' personal data.

The extension may store limited local extension state in the user's browser, including:
- deletion count
- license unlock status
- license key, if the user chooses to enter one
- local UI state related to selected conversations

This data is stored using Chrome extension storage and is used only to provide the extension's user-facing features.

## Website Access

f-gemini-delete requests access to https://gemini.google.com/ only to display batch selection controls and perform user-triggered delete actions on the Gemini web page.

The extension does not read Gemini chat content for profiling, advertising, analytics, or resale. Delete actions are performed only after the user selects conversations and triggers the delete operation.

## License Validation

If the user enters a license key, the extension sends the license key to the license validation endpoint:

https://api.lemonsqueezy.com/v1/licenses/validate

This request is used only to validate the license and unlock paid functionality. The extension does not send Gemini chat content to this endpoint.

## How We Use Data

Data handled by the extension is used only to:
- enable multi-select mode
- track selected conversations during the current workflow
- run user-triggered deletion actions
- show deletion progress
- store local extension state
- validate license status when applicable

## Data Sharing

f-gemini-delete does not sell, rent, or share user data with advertisers, data brokers, or analytics providers.

The only external data transfer is license validation, when the user voluntarily submits a license key. That transfer is used solely to validate the license.

## Limited Use Disclosure

f-gemini-delete's use of information received from Chrome extension permissions complies with the Chrome Web Store User Data Policy, including the Limited Use requirements.

The extension only uses requested permissions to provide or improve its single purpose: helping users batch manage and delete Gemini web chat history. The extension does not use user data for advertising, creditworthiness, profiling, or unrelated purposes.

## Data Security

License validation requests are sent over HTTPS. Local extension state is stored using Chrome extension storage.

## User Control

Users can stop using the extension at any time by disabling or uninstalling it from Chrome. Uninstalling the extension removes extension-managed local data according to Chrome's extension storage behavior.

## Contact

For privacy-related questions, contact the developer through the support contact provided on the Chrome Web Store listing.
